President Muhammadu Buhari has approved two new appointments at the Oil and Gas Free Zones Authority (OGFZA) and the Revenue Mobilisation, Allocation and Fiscal Commission (RMAFC). A statement by the Director of Information in the Office of the Secretary to the Government of the Federation (OSGF), Mr. Willie Bassey, said the President also approved the re-appointment of Captain Junaid Abdullahi as the Executive Secretary of the Border Communities Development Agency (BCDA), for a final four-year term. “President Buhari has approved the following new appointments: Tijjani Yahaya Kaura, Managing Director of Oil and Gas Free Zones Authority (OGFZA), for an initial term of three years effective from July 18;   Abdulrazaq declares July 29 work-free for voters…     Bryann plots against level two housemates     Chief Judge jails lawyer for alleged contempt   “Mr. Augustine Chukwu Umahi, Secretary, Revenue Mobilisation, Allocation and Fiscal Commission (RMAFC) for an initial term of four years from July 6, 2022. “Also, President Buhari has approved the renewal of the appointment of Captain Junaid Abdullahi, Executive Secretary, Border Communities Development Agency (BCDA), for a final term of four years with effect from September 22, 2022. “The President congratulated all the appointees and urged them to bring their wealth of experience to bear on their appointments,” the statement said.